metadata.Title: CVE-2023-5129 on Ubuntu 23.10 (mantic) - medium
metadata.Description:
** REJECT ** This CVE ID has been rejected or withdrawn by its CVENumbering Authority. Duplicate of CVE-2023-4863.

    Update Instructions:

    Run `sudo pro fix CVE-2023-5129` to fix the vulnerability. The problem can be corrected
    by updating your system to the following package versions:

libwebp7 - 1.2.4-0.3
libwebpdemux2 - 1.2.4-0.3
libwebpmux3 - 1.2.4-0.3
webp - 1.2.4-0.3
No subscription required

criterions.comment: libwebp package in mantic, is related to the CVE in some way and has been fixed (note: '1.2.4-0.3').
